article.headline: Liberty 71, William &amp, Mary 62
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Evan Gordon scored 19 points and John Brown had a double-double as Liberty defeated William & Mary 71-62 on Saturday night. The Tribe (4-6) has been holding opponents to 36.4 percent shooting over their last six games and continued to do so against the Flames, limiting them to 37.9 percent in the first half (11 of 29). Liberty (7-5), which trailed 33-27 at halftime, then shot 57.9 percent in the second half, outscoring William & Mary 44-29. Trailing 33-27, Liberty went on a 13-6 run to lead 40-39 on Gordon's layup with 14:12 to go. William & Mary regained the lead by one 51 seconds later but Brown's jumper put the Flames up for good, 42-41, with 13:12 left. Brown finished with 14 points and 12 rebounds. Quinn McDowell and Matt Rum scored 15 points each for the Tribe, who went 1 of 12 from 3 (8.3 percent) in the second half hitting 7 of 14 in the first.
